  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BRACED Burkina Faso Intermon Oxfam</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BRACED will consolidate and scale up two tested methodologies (DFID/CA) for climate adaptation and building resilience, incorporating lessons and new partners and innovations. It found a major barrier to sustained change is the lack of access to appropriate and timely information and the space to challenge behavioural norms over time. By supporting the M&#xE9;t&#xE9;o Burkina and local media we will increase the quality and quantity of reliable, regular and user friendly climate information tailored for at-risk communities, particularly women and girls, and work with them to develop practical solutions for transformational change to build resilience to climate variability and disasters.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Main activities include:
-	Build and refine climate services in Burkina Faso in response to user needs
-	Increase availability and quality of relevant information on weather and climate change at national level
-	Increase availability and quality of relevant information on weather and climate change at local level
-	Local Participatory Approach for risk management
-	Building local productive capacity through implementation of Soils and Water Conservation activities to mitigate climate risk 
-	Development, support and monitoring of IGA for the diversification of income sources 
-	Multi-seasonal promotion of market garden production &amp; diet diversification
-	Mitigation of climate-related prices increase  for the poorest
-	BRACED Participatory Approach for institutional risk management in 13 communes 
-	Collective community mobilization for disaster risk reduction
-	Conflict prevention on pastoral resources (water, land, fodder)
-	Community awareness on practical solutions to build nutritional resilience
-	Academic and policy research agenda
-	Spaces for internal and external dialogue, advocacy and learning
-	Specific impact studies on good practices to face climate extremes disasters</narrative>
  </description>
